    <item>
      <title>About those potions</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12008#M12008</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;Ok, so every melee class PK specialist is buying gate potions, snare potions, heal potions, SOW potions, etc so that they can add those abilities to their ability to melee.  In effect it gives them some of the key things that a caster can do PVP on top of all the things that a melee can do.  I have two suggestions short of removing these from the game that might help.  Don't know how hard these would be to implement, maybe Pinhead could comment:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Suggestion1:&lt;/strong&gt;  Introduce &amp;quot;melee&amp;quot; potions.  If a melee can snare, and SOW, and gate, how about a potion that lets my pet quad for 500 and crit-hit for 2000 occasionally for two minutes?  That should even things up a bit.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Suggestion2:&lt;/strong&gt;  Use the same skill check on potions that the underlying spell uses if cast.  If a spell typically uses alteration and you try to use a potion that casts that spell and you are a melee, your skill (obviously) will be zero.  Have them fizzle at the same rate that they would if a zero-skill caster tried to cast the same spell.  That should put enough risk in using the pots that people would think twice (or not use them at all) unless they were a caster who had the underlying skill.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Some other things (such as procs on weapons) need a little tweaking too, I think.  I zoned in to Neriak yesterday and before I had control of my toon a monk started whacking me with a stick that dispelled every buff I had in a couple of seconds.  Faster than a caster could dispell someone of that many buffs, for sure.  I don't know if he just got a lucky string of procs or what, but if that stick always does that, it probably needs to be adjusted so that at the very least it can't be used to insta-debuff people at zone-lines.  If it procs a debuff, it should take the normal casting time for a debuff to work, and should be interrupted if he moves during that time, no?&lt;/div&gt;</description>
