      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12227#M12227</link>
      <description>Suggestions of nerfing and removing potions need to be ignored. They are not a significant balance issue when viewed relatively.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Casters benefit from many of these potions as well. I happen to know a mage who lives and dies by snare clickies. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Also, any healing potion can be easily outDPSed at its requisite level.&#xD;
They prolong fights, they only tip the scales if you're gimp, in my&#xD;
opinion. If someone beats you because you're carrying a potion, you&#xD;
have a problem. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Also, if we're going to go after a healing item for removal on Zek,&#xD;
let's get rid of the Prayers of Life first. Full HP insta-heals for the&#xD;
plat-rich. Much larger issue than two-minute recharge, mid-quality heal&#xD;
elixirs.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
And seeing as casters have far less HP than melees, I will say that&#xD;
said heal potions have saved my caster toons' rear ends many times and&#xD;
allowed them enough time to break a snare or root and get to shadow&#xD;
stepping, nuking, DoTing, whatever was called for again.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
