      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well, about the only suggestion that I have right now is to put mana regen potions into the game that are as powerful as the heal pots.  Would make for some really, really, long fights that would prove nothing other than who could buy the most pots.  I got attacked by a ranger today.  Had him under 30% a couple of times using some tips that Skelkus gave me (thank you Skelkus), but at the end of the day, he potted me right out of mana.  That's the real downside of these pots.  If you're a melee and I'm a caster we can both hit them, but when I'm OOM you've still got a sword and a range weapon, and about the best I can do is cuss at you. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an aside, how come a melee doesn't run out of stamina as fast as I run out of mana?  He can whack away all day long, pretty much, unless he pops some discs that are big stamina hits.   Maybe that's the way to neutralize the effect of the pots.  Adjust it so that hitting me for 1000 with a sword takes as much stamina as me hitting you for 1000 with a spell takes mana.  Then after you and I have both heal potted each other to a standstill, we can just stand there and look at each other until we med up.  Could make for some all-day fights, but what the hell.  It would be an improvement over the current state of affairs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
